1.2 Plate reader data normalization

  • Step 1, background OD730 correction:
    • Calculate average OD730 of blank wells for each timepoint
    • Subtract blank average OD730 from the rest of the wells for each timepoint
  • Step 2, EVC normalization:
    • For each timepoint, calculate the average raw fluorescence / OD730 of ALL the EVC wells
    • For each timepoint, calculate raw fluorescence / OD730 for each well
    • For each timepoint, subtract the average EVC fluorescence / OD730 from the fluorescence / OD730 of each well

This step corrects for autofluorescence and background fluorescence at the same time and it also normalizes for the biomass.

  • Step 3, summarize:
    • Take the average of the background corrected fluorescence / OD730 caculated in the previous step, for each experiment, strain, condition and timepoint.
  • Step 4, 0 to 1 normalization:
    • For each experiment, normalize the average ratios calculated previously from 0 to 1 by using the min max method: \(\frac{\frac{F}{OD_{730}} - min(\frac{F}{OD_{730}})}{ max(\frac{F}{OD_{730}}) - min(\frac{F}{OD_{730}})}\)

This step allows to compare the ratios between labs.
